An unidentified man’s body was discovered in a sugar cane field at Inanda, KwaZulu-Natal on Monday morning. Spokesperson for the Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA), Prem Balram, said they received a call from a farmer after they made the discovery. “RUSA medics examined the deceased who was lying on his stomach on an unpaved road. He sustained a gunshot wound to his head and right arm. The motive for the murder has not yet been established,” said Balram.